1.  A system for the digital issuance of community tax certificates and permits, comprising:
    a. a user digital wallet configured to store decentralized identifiers (DIDs) and verifiable credentials (VCs);
    b. a government issuer node configured to receive applications and sign VCs;
    c. a blockchain layer comprising smart contracts for managing payment settlements and credential provenance; and
    d. a machine learning risk engine configured to analyze user data and output a dynamic validity period;
    wherein the smart contract is configured to atomically execute a payment transaction and the issuance of the VC simultaneously, wherein the expiration date of the VC is determined by the output of the machine learning risk engine prior to the transaction finalization.

4.  A method for issuing a digital community tax certificate, comprising the steps of:
    a. receiving a request from a user digital wallet;
    b. retrieving user historical data from a centralized government database;
    c. processing said user historical data through a machine learning model to generate a compliance risk score;
    d. determining a certificate validity duration based on said compliance risk score;
    e. initiating a blockchain smart contract transaction requesting payment of a tax fee;
    f. verifying the payment within the smart contract;
    g. upon successful payment verification, generating a Verifiable Credential signed by the government issuer node containing the determined certificate validity duration; and
    h. transmitting said Verifiable Credential to the user digital wallet.

